{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-80ad9b3a-37af-97bb-8bf7-7d2e15a098e3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"auto","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I got drug info. Let me also check for throat-related medications and maybe some other useful drugs.\n\nNow let me think about the prescription:\n\n**Patient summary:**\n- 32F, 58kg, acute upper respiratory tract infection (viral)\n- Symptoms: sore throat, mild cough with white sputum, low fever (38.2°C)\n- Previous treatment: moxifloxacin + azithromycin IV for 1 day → palpitations → stopped\n- Labs: WBC 6.8 (normal), N% 58 (normal), CRP 8.4 (normal)\n- No allergies, normal renal/hepatic function, not pregnant\n- Physical exam: mild throat congestion, no pus, tonsils grade I, lungs clear\n\n**My prescription plan:**\n\n1. **对乙酰氨基酚 (Paracetamol)** — NRDL A, for fever and sore throat, PRN when temp >38.5°C or throat pain bothersome\n   - Dose: 0.5g per dose, PO, PRN (or bid for sore throat)\n   - Actually, current temp is 38.2°C, but it can spike. PRN is appropriate.\n   - Standard adult dose: 500mg per dose, up to every 4-6 hours, max 2g/day (conservative)\n   - Specification: 0.5g/片\n   - Let me prescribe: 0.5g, PO, prn, 0 days (PRN), instructions: 体温>38.5℃或咽痛明显时服用，每日不超过4次\n\nActually wait - for sore throat and fever, a regular dosing might be more appropriate for the sore throat. Let me think...\n\nFor acute sore throat pain, regular dosing of paracetamol is more effective than PRN. But since the fever is low-grade (38.2°C) and likely viral, I think PRN is fine. The patient can take it when throat pain is bothersome or fever spikes.\n\nLet me also consider:\n- For cough - it's mild with small white sputum. Dextromethorphan is an option but cough isn't the main complaint and it's mild. I might skip this or add it as PRN.\n- Actually, the chief complaint says \"咳嗽咽痛\" so both are important. But the cough is described as \"咳少量白痰\" - small amount white sputum. An antitussive might suppress useful cough for clearing secretions. Maybe better to not suppress it, or use an expectorant instead.\n\nLet me reconsider - I'll keep it simple:\n1. **对乙酰氨基酚** for fever and sore throat (PRN)\n2. Maybe skip cough medicine since it's mild productive cough (suppressing cough with dextromethorphan when there's sputum isn't ideal)\n\nActually, let me also check for an expectorant or throat spray.\n\nLet me check a few more drugs.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"39d4f938-b65e-43dd-95fb-61925d54e32e","session_id":"a08d8111-c003-466b-97a2-5b924a979b4b"}
